\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b1\i0 Peer Review Quality Standards}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The Editorial Review Operations Team ensures a high quality, rigorous and efficient peer-review process for all manuscripts submitted to Frontiers. The team establishes and upholds the\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.frontiersin.org/about/review-system#FrontiersFullReview"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 peer-review guidelines}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \~for editors, reviewers and authors, which incorporate the best practices and\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.frontiersin.org/about/review-system#EditorialPolicies"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 editorial policies}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The team is responsible for upholding the following quality standards:}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sb180\ltrch\loch \ls8\ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Editors and reviewers are experts in the subject of the manuscript, with necessary expertise to evaluate the research by having established a sufficient research work or publication record on the same or related research area;}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\ltrch\loch \ls8\ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Editors and reviewers have no relationship to the authors and/or research that would affect the objectivity of the peer-review process;}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 In case the peer review is ongoing, and it is discovered that editors or reviewers do not have the relevant expertise or have a conflict-of-interest, they can be revoked and replaced during review by the Peer Review Team and/or the editor;}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Reviewers thoroughly complete the subject-specific questionnaire provided to assess the scientific rigour, quality and validity of the manuscript they are reviewing. Review reports are verified to ensure they provide a constructive assessment of the manuscripts\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92 validity and quality to the authors;}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Final editorial checks to verify that the peer-review process adhered to the quality standards, that the reviewers\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92 and editor\u8217\'92s concerns have been addressed and that the manuscript is ready for publication;}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sa180\ltrch\loch \ls8\ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Only high-quality manuscripts that pass our\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.frontiersin.org/about/review-system#AcceptanceCriteria"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 acceptance criteria}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \~are published.}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \~}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 In accepting a peer-review assignment with Frontiers, editors and reviewers agree to:}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sb180\ltrch\loch \ls9\ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 1.	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Have the necessary expertise to judge the manuscript\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s quality, rigour and validity;}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\ltrch\loch \ls9\ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 2.	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Submit thorough, high-quality review reports;}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 3.	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Provide feedback in a timely manner, remaining responsive to collaborate with the authors;}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sa180\ltrch\loch \ls9\ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 4.	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Behave in a professional, ethical way and be constructive during interactions with the editors, authors and editorial team.}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \~}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 In parallel, for manuscripts to remain under consideration for publication, the authors must:}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sb180\ltrch\loch \ls10\ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 1.	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Remain engaged with the peer-review process and responsive for queries from the editors, reviewers or Frontiers Editorial Office;}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sa180\ltrch\loch \ls10\ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 2.	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Behave in a professional way, use constructive, respectful language when communicating with the editorial board members, reviewers or Frontiers Editorial Office, and collaborate effectively during the peer-review process.}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Participants in the peer review will be removed from their assignments if they do not adhere to and meet these review standards. Manuscripts can also be rejected should the authors be unresponsive for an extended period of time (30 days) or use inappropriate, offensive language when communicating with the Editorial Board members or Frontiers Editorial Office.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b1\i0 Pillars of Peer Review}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The Frontiers Collaborative Review provides and guarantees:}
\par\pard\plain \sa60\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs20\b1\i0 Collaborative Review}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Our Collaborative Review Forum unites authors, reviewers and the handling Editor (called the Associate Editor for editorial board members, or Topic Editor for Research Topics) \endash  and if need be the Specialty Chief Editor \endash  in a direct online dialogue, enabling quick iterations and facilitating consensus. Editors and reviewers work with the authors to improve their manuscript.}
\par\pard\plain \sa60\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs20\b1\i0 Objective Review}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Frontiers promotes a strict separation between review and evaluation. Frontiers editors and reviewers have the mandate to focus on objective criteria evaluating the quality, rigour and validity of the study and to ensure that the results are valid, the analysis is correct, and the quality high. We publish all papers assessed to be valid and of good quality. Reviewers may recommend rejection based upon objective errors and the criteria for rejection. Judgments regarding the importance of a paper can be made through open post-publication reviews. We also use objective impact metrics \endash  reflecting the opinion of the entire community \endash  to spotlight outstanding discoveries.}
\par\pard\plain \sa60\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs20\b1\i0 Rigorous Review}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Frontiers provides a review questionnaire template to make reviews systematic and convene the efforts of reviewers on objective issues. The review must focus solely on the quality of both the research and the manuscript, and must aim at providing constructive comments to bring the final paper to its best quality. This allows fair, rapid, comprehensive and comparable assessment of research. The evaluation of the research will be done successively by means of the article-level impact metrics. Moreover, Frontiers provides authors with the highest quality review service by assigning only the world\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s top researchers to the Frontiers\u8217\'92 Chief and Associate Editorial Boards.}
\par\pard\plain \sa60\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs20\b1\i0 Transparent Review}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 To guarantee the most rigorous and objective reviews, the identities of reviewers remain anonymous during the review period. When a manuscript is accepted for publication, the names of the reviewers who endorsed its publication appear on the published article,\~}{\f2\fs24\b1\i0 without exceptions}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 . If a reviewer recommends rejection or withdraws during any stage of this process, his/her name will\~}{\f2\fs24\b1\i0 not}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \~be disclosed. The handling Editor\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s name is also made public on the published article, acknowledging their contribution.\line As a result of this process, reviews are conducted constructively, with editors and reviewers holding a level of accountability and responsibility for the paper by providing rigorous feedback that delivers the highest possible quality publication. Please also note that, as Frontiers operates a single-blind peer review process, the authors\u8217\'92 identities are known to the reviewers.}
\par\pard\plain \sa60\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs20\b1\i0 Efficient Review}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Frontiers\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92 publishing platform is custom-built. We offer one of the fastest systems amongst academic publishers. Our Collaborative Review Forum guides authors, reviewers and editors smoothly through the review process and alerts them when any action is required. This has shortened the average time from submission to final decision to 90 days.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b1\i0 Full Peer Review Guidelines}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The full Frontiers Collaborative Peer Review consists of two phases.}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch \ls11\ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs24\b1\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f2\fs24\b1\i0 Independent Review}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \line During the Independent Review phase, the reviewers assess the manuscript independently from each other and from the authors, according to a standardized review template. These templates are adapted to each article type.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs24\b1\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f2\fs24\b1\i0 Interactive Review}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \line During the Interactive Review phase, authors and reviewers can interact with each other through real-time comments in the discussion forum \endash  with the aim of addressing all concerns about the manuscript. The handling Editor oversees the review process, and, if required, the Specialty Chief Editor can also enter the Review Forum.}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The following articles types undergo a full peer review:}
\par\plain {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Original%20Research"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Original Research}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Review"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Review}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Brief%20Research%20Report"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Brief Research Report}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Case%20Report"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Case Report}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Clinical%20Study%20Protocol"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Clinical Trial}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Community%20Case%20Study"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Community Case Study}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Conceptual%20Analysis"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Conceptual Analysis}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Curriculum%20Instruction%20&amp="}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Curriculum Instruction and Pedagogy}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#DataReport"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Data Report}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#General%20Commentary"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 General Commentaries}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Hypothesis%20&%20Theory"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Hypothesis & Theory Articles}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Methods"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Methods}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Mini%20Review"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Mini Review}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Opinion"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Opinion}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Policy%20&amp"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Policy and Practice Review}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Policy%20Brief"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Policy Brief}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Perspective"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Perspective}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Registered%20Report"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Registered Report}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Study%20Protocol"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Study Protocol}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Technology%20&%20Code"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Technology & Code}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Systematic%20Reviews"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Systematic Reviews}}
\par\pard\plain \sa60\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs20\b1\i0 Post-Submission Steps}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Once a manuscript is submitted, the Frontiers Editorial Office conducts a pre-screening for validation of research integrity and quality standards. If a manuscript meets Frontiers\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92 quality criteria, an Editor from the relevant specialty section is invited to handle the manuscript\u8217\'92s peer-review process. After a preliminary content check, the editor decides whether to send the manuscript for review or to recommend it for immediate rejection to the Specialty Chief Editor.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 In the latter case, the Specialty Chief Editor may confirm the handling Editor\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s recommendation of immediate rejection due to the following reasons:}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sb180\ltrch\loch \ls12\ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Objective errors in the methods, applications, or interpretations were identified in the manuscript that prevent further consideration}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\ltrch\loch \ls12\ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Ethical issues were identified in the manuscript that prevent further review or publication}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sa180\ltrch\loch \ls12\ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The content of this manuscript does not meet the standards of rigor required by the journal to be considered for publication (see full\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.frontiersin.org/about/review-system#RejectionCriteria"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 rejection criteria}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \~above)}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The Specialty Chief Editor may, nevertheless, override the handling Editor's recommendation and decide that the manuscript deserves being reviewed before a final decision is made. In this case he/she will assign the manuscript to a new handling Editor for another assessment.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The handling Editor invites experts to review the manuscript; most article types require at least two reviewers to complete a review. These reviewers can either be invited from the Frontiers Board of Review Editors or appropriately recruited among experts in the field.}
\par\pard\plain \sa60\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs20\b1\i0 Independent Review Phase}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The reviewers are asked to submit the standardized\~}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 Frontiers Independent Review Report}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \~via the online Collaborative Review Forum within 10 days after accepting the assignment. This is done independently by each reviewer. The handling Editor is automatically notified as soon as each of the\~}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 Independent Review Reports}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \~is submitted.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Once all reviewers have submitted an\~}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 Independent Review Report}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 , the Editor is responsible for activating the next phase, i.e. the Interactive Review, to release the review reports to the authors. If the Editor would like to recommend rejection during the Independent Review phase, they can do so by activating the Interactive Review phase with major concerns, providing the authors with the reports and a unique opportunity for rebuttal during a defined timeframe.}
\par\pard\plain \sa60\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs20\b1\i0 Interactive Review Phase}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Once the editor activates the Interactive Review phase, authors are immediately notified and granted access to the Collaborative Review Forum, where they are able to view the reviewers' comments. Authors are asked to respond and/or submit a revised manuscript within 12, 17 or 21 days, depending on the level of revisions requested by the editor. If the authors are unresponsive to multiple communication attempts, the Frontiers Editorial Office will send a final email to the authors with a 7-day deadline to respond. Following this, the Editorial Office reserves the right to withdraw the manuscript from the review process.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The Editor can access and post comments in the Collaborative Review Forum at any time. Additionally, the Editor monitors the discussions occurring between authors and reviewers within the Forum and ensures not only the timeliness, but also the constructiveness, of the participants\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92 interactions.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Should a dispute arise at this stage, the Editor must act as a mediator, working with all parties involved to resolve the issues and even inviting new reviewers for further opinions if needed. If the disagreement persists, the Specialty Chief Editor is then invited to enter the Interactive Review phase, assess the situation, and take a final decision as to whether the review should be ended by rejecting the manuscript or continued \endash  potentially, but not necessarily, with a new handling Editor and set of reviewers.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 When a disagreement cannot be resolved to the satisfaction of a reviewer, he/she can choose to recommend rejection of the manuscript. The handling Editor is then informed of the rejection recommendation and the reason. A reviewer can also withdraw from the review at any time. In both cases of rejection recommendation and withdrawal, the reviewer will no longer participate in the Review Forum, but may continue to follow the manuscript status under their My Frontiers page. The Editor is informed of the reviewer recommendations and may choose to further recommend rejection to the chief editor, or invite other reviewers to receive additional expert opinions. If a reviewer submitted an Independent Review Report prior to withdrawal or rejection recommendation, the report will be maintained in the Review Forum for participants to access throughout the review process. It is not removed or lost.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 During this phase, a manuscript may be rejected at any point for the following reasons:}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch \ls13\ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Objective errors in the methods, applications, or interpretations were identified in this manuscript that prevent further consideration;}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Ethical issues were identified in this manuscript that prevent further review or publication;}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The content of this manuscript does not meet the standards of rigor required by the journal to be considered for publication;}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The manuscript could not be sufficiently revised by the authors to address the concerns raised by the reviewers or editor during the review process;}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Other reasons that meet the\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.frontiersin.org/about/review-system#RejectionCriteria"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 rejection criteria}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The review is complete only once all reviewer and editor comments have been satisfactorily addressed by the authors.}
\par\pard\plain \sa60\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs20\b1\i0 Arbitrations}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Should a dispute arise that may result in the rejection of the manuscript, the authors may trigger an arbitration. In the first place, the handling Editor will mediate and involve all reviewers in a discussion aimed at resolving the dispute.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 If a resolution cannot be agreed upon, the Specialty Chief Editor is alerted and can opt to bring in additional reviewers and handling Editor for consultation. A manuscript must be rejected if the arbitration rules that any of the\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.frontiersin.org/about/review-system#RejectionCriteria"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 rejection criteria}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \~are met.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Reviewers are entitled to trigger an arbitration, too, if they judge that the authors are reluctant to make required changes. Reviewers may of course recommend rejection at any time or withdraw from the review process if they disagree with the arbitration ruling (in both cases their identity remains undisclosed). The withdrawal of a reviewer requires the recruitment of a new one, which slows down the process. Therefore, authors are encouraged to cooperate as much as possible in addressing the concerns of the reviewers involved with their manuscript. Should an arbitration rule in favor of the authors, then the manuscript can be accepted even if there was a previous rejection recommendation.}
\par\pard\plain \sa60\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs20\b1\i0 Manuscript Acceptance}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 If the reviewers endorse the publication of the manuscript in its current form, they must finalize their\~}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 Interactive Review Reports}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 , which automatically notifies the handling Editor. For acceptance to be considered, the manuscript must:}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch \ls14\ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Be VALID as defined in the\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.frontiersin.org/about/review-system#AcceptanceCriteria"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 acceptance criteria}}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Have an Editor and the minimum number of independent reviewers assigned for the article type}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Be endorsed by a majority of the assigned, non-withdrawn reviewers}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The Editor can then either accept the final version of the manuscript or request further changes as necessary, typically within a few days. Acceptance of a manuscript can be decided by the handling Editor and does not require the approval of the Specialty Chief Editor.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Acceptance by the handling Editor moves the article into the Final Validation phase, during which Frontiers\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92 in-house Peer Review Team performs final technical and quality checks, including whether the review was performed adequately. Should the manuscript fail the final checks, it can either be put back into review to address the identified issue(s) or else the provisional acceptance decision can be overridden and the manuscript will be rejected at this stage without publication.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The Article Processing Charge (APC) is payable within 30 days of acceptance and is required before final publication of the manuscript.}
\par\pard\plain \sa60\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs20\b1\i0 Manuscript Rejection}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 If the minimum required number of reviewers to endorse the manuscript is not met (usually two, and must be a majority), then the handling Editor must recommend to the Specialty Chief Editor that the manuscript be rejected for publication. The final rejection decision is usually made by the Specialty Chief Editor but can also be made by the Frontiers Research Integrity Team based on the\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.frontiersin.org/about/review-system#RejectionCriteria"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 rejection criteria}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 If a manuscript is rejected, no Article Processing Charges or other fee is charged.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b1\i0 Short Peer Review Guidelines}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The following articles types are attributed a shortened peer review:}
\par\plain {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Editorial"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Editorials}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Book%20Review"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Book Reviews}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 , and\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.frontiersin.org/Genetics/articletype#Classification"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf4 Classifications}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Short peer reviews differ from full peer reviews in two aspects: they are directly forwarded to the Interactive Review Phase and they may be reviewed by the handling Editor alone. It is up to the Editor\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s consideration if further reviewers are invited to the review process.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Therefore, following submission, an Editor of the relevant Frontiers Specialty is immediately invited to take on the manuscript editorial assignment, which encompasses the role of the reviewer, too. Since no Independent Review Report is required, the manuscript enters the Interactive Review Phase immediately.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Interactive Review, manuscript acceptance and rejection follow the same rules as for full peer reviews.}
